cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and discourse relations. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel neural network architecture. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves modeling language and making predictions. The use of recurrent neural networks also suggests it could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions dialog act classification, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as dialog acts are often used in video and audio analysis.
